<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1532,1917]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
This small genus has been considered to comprise five species of large skippers (
<bibRefCitation author="Ackery, P. R. &amp; Smith, C. R. &amp; Vane-Wright, R. I." box="[1099,1323,1532,1557]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref33789" refString="Ackery, P. R., Smith, C. R. &amp; Vane-Wright, R. I. (1995) Carcasson's African Butterflies. An annotated catalogue of the Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea of the Afrotropical Region. CSIRO Publications, Melbourne, Australia, 803 pp." type="book" year="1995">
Ackery 
<emphasis box="[1194,1246,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. 1995
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindsey, A. W." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="75 - 106" refId="ref36075" refString="Lindsey, A. W. (1925) The types of hesperioid genera. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 18, 75 - 106." type="journal article" year="1925">Lindsey (1925)</bibRefCitation>
made 
<taxonomicName authority="(Trimen)" baseAuthorityName="Trimen" box="[300,563,1567,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysmephila">
<emphasis box="[300,457,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. dysmephila</emphasis>
(Trimen)
</taxonomicName>
the 
<typeStatus box="[612,660,1568,1592]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus. All food plant records from this genus are from palms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1532,1917]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
In the French West African literature on palm pests, early records of 
<taxonomicName box="[1025,1186,1639,1664]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysmephila">
<emphasis box="[1025,1186,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. dysmephila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear to have been misidentifications for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hewitson)" baseAuthorityName="Hewitson" box="[400,670,1676,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[400,533,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
(Hewitson)
</taxonomicName>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mabille)" baseAuthorityName="Mabille" box="[811,1081,1676,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quaternata">
<emphasis box="[811,965,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. quaternata</emphasis>
(Mabille)
</taxonomicName>
, which is closest in appearance (see below). 
<taxonomicName box="[295,535,1711,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[295,535,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Zophopetes cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
replaces 
<taxonomicName box="[641,799,1711,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysmephila">
<emphasis box="[641,799,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. dysmephila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in more recent publications on palm pests (
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Desmier de Chenon, R. &amp; Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="169 - 228" refId="ref36432" refString="Mariau, D., Desmier de Chenon, R., Julia, J. F. &amp; Philippe, R. (1981) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier en Afrique Occidentale. Oil palm and coconut pests in West Africa. Oleagineux, 36, 169 - 228." type="journal article" year="1981">
Mariau 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. 1981
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[221,368,1748,1773]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref36315" refString="Mariau, D. (2000) Les ravageurs du palmier a huile et du cocotier: biologie, description et methodes de lutte. CIRAD, Montpellier, France, 1 disque optique numerique, CD-ROM." type="book" year="2000">Mariau 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D." box="[380,440,1748,1773]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref36353" refString="Mariau, D. (2001) The fauna of oil palm and coconut: insect and mites pests and their natural enemies. CIRAD, Montpellier, 264 pp." type="book" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
), and the descriptions of the early stages (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[960,1212,1748,1773]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin 1974</bibRefCitation>
) match 
<taxonomicName box="[1303,1436,1749,1772]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[1303,1436,1749,1772]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName box="[282,441,1783,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysmephila">
<emphasis box="[282,441,1783,1808]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. dysmephila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the records of 
<taxonomicName box="[696,856,1783,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysmephila">
<emphasis box="[696,856,1783,1808]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. dysmephila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from oil palm (
<taxonomicName box="[1041,1238,1783,1808]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Elaeis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis box="[1041,1238,1783,1808]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Elaeis guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) at Anguédedou, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,304,1820,1845]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Côte d’Ivoire</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Genty, P." box="[323,463,1820,1845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="645 - 648" refId="ref34982" refString="Genty, P. (1968) Deux lepidopteres nuisibles au palmier a huile. Oleagineux, 23 (11), 645 - 648." type="journal article" year="1968">Genty 1968</bibRefCitation>
), and as pests of oil palm and coconut in West Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P." box="[1119,1383,1820,1845]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="187 - 188" refId="ref36384" refString="Mariau, D. &amp; Morin, J. P. (1974) Les ravageurs et maladies du palmier a huile et du cocotier. Chenilles defoliatrices de la famille des Hesperidae en Afrique Occidentale. Oleagineux, 29 (4), 187 - 188." type="journal article" year="1974">Mariau &amp; Morin 1974</bibRefCitation>
) are considered to be of 
<taxonomicName box="[372,504,1856,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerymica">
<emphasis box="[372,504,1856,1880]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. cerymica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the record of 
<taxonomicName box="[785,942,1855,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysmephila">
<emphasis box="[785,942,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. dysmephila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[1010,1209,1855,1880]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Phoenix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reclinata">
<emphasis box="[1010,1209,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Phoenix reclinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Lamto (
<bibRefCitation author="Vuattoux, R." pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="562 - 568" refId="ref37364" refString="Vuattoux, R. (1999) Les lepidopteres hesperiides de la Station de Lamto (Cote d'Ivoire). Lambillionea, 94, 562 - 568." type="journal article" year="1999">Vuattoux 1999</bibRefCitation>
), is referable to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Larsen 2005)" baseAuthorityName="Larsen" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[391,712,1892,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Zophopetes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quaternata">
<emphasis box="[391,543,1893,1916]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Z. quaternata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Larsen, T. B." box="[558,704,1892,1917]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref35885" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. 2 Vols. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, Denmark, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">Larsen 2005</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
